FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1777227067
OL,3,CRow over Bobby Sands Belfast statue
OL,5,F"Unionists had no problem with illegal
OL,6,Fmonuments, plaques, murals and
OL,7,Fmemorial gardens in largely working
OL,8,Fclass loyalist areas."
OL,10,FIn a statement an SDLP spokesperson
OL,11,Fsaid: "The SDLP recognises the
OL,12,Fcomplexity of legacy and identity, and
OL,13,Fhas consistently supported the all-
OL,14,Fparty FICT proposals as a framework
OL,15,Ffor addressing the past in the present
OL,16,Fday.
OL,26,@mD@AOUpD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1777227067
OL,3,CRow over Bobby Sands Belfast statue
OL,5,F"Once again major parties on council
OL,6,Fhave focused on distraction and
OL,7,Fconflict issues, and SDLP councillors
OL,8,Foffered an amendment to resolve the
OL,9,Fmatter. If it had passed, the issue
OL,10,Fwould have been closed and the DUP
OL,11,Fmotion never would have come to a
OL,12,Fvote. It is for Sinn Fein to explain
OL,13,Fwhy they opposed the SDLP proposal.
OL,15,F"Planning laws exist to ensure
OL,16,Fconsistency, fairness and public buy
OL,17,Fin and we believe that system should
OL,18,Fbe used where available.
OL,26,@tD@Wrr
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1777227067
OL,3,CRow over Bobby Sands Belfast statue
OL,5,F"Comments by others to blame the SDLP
OL,6,Fon any aspect of this issue should be
OL,7,Fseen for what they are, a deflection."
OL,9,FDUP councillor Dean McCullough said
OL,10,Fthe motion introduced at council was
OL,11,Fconcerned about "equality".
OL,13,FHe said: "The public want to know that
OL,14,Fthe same rules apply to everyone."
OL,16,FSinn Fein Councillor Ciaran Beattie
OL,17,Fsaid the motion was an "attack on the
OL,18,Frights of republicans to remember
OL,19,Ftheir dead".
OL,26,@sD@QOUsD@ZO]uD@JOUvD@bO]xD@GqryD@XOU{D@
OL,26,AKO]
